speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs (1) if he is aware of the International Commission's decision to authorise South Vietnam to replace armaments taken


away by the French Union troops during their withdrawal from South Vietnam; and to what extent, as co-Chairman of the Commission. his approval was sought arid given;

(2) what replacement of weapons or troops there has been in South Vietnam since the withdrawal of the French forces after the Geneva Agreement.
